resources.string: This character is skilled at instructing steamjacks to act. The \'jack marshal must know the cortex\'s native language to instrcut it as well as the \'jack\'s cortex lock codes. Bonded steamjacks cannot be affected by this ability.
The character gains an extra quick action during each of their turns that can only be used to drive a \'jack
The character can advance through other characters if they have enough movement to move completely past the other characters\' bases. The character also gains +3 on Jumping skill rolls.
While B2B with this character, friendly characters gain +1 to their command range.
During the first round of an encounter, this character gains boosted attack and damage rolls against enemies that have not yet activated
When this character hits a living target with a melee attack but the damage roll fails to exceed the target\'s ARM, the target suffers d3 damage points instead of the damage rolled.
If no melee damage, d3 damage
This character can judge the value of most fine goods with an inspection. Truly good fakes might require a Detection + INT roll to spot.
Can value goods at a glance
When making attacks, this character ignores focus points overboosting the target\'s Power Field and spell effects adding to its ARM or DEF.
This character gains +3 ARM against magic attacks
This character can reroll failed Mechanikal Engineering rolls. Each failed roll can be rerolled only once as a result of Arcane Engineer.
When this character forfeits their movement to aim with a ranged weapon, they ignore stealth that turn.
This character can have a number of spells equal to INTx3, rather than INTx2
This character can reroll failed Detection rols. Each failed roll can be rerolled only once as a result of Astute.
This character gains an additional die on their back strike damage rolls.
This character can use one battle plan during each turn without spending a feat point.

The character can spend one feat point to use this ability. Using a battle plan is a quick action. When a character uses this battle plan, each friendly character in this character\'s command range who is under their command and is knocked down immediately stands up or goes prone.

The character can spend one feat point to use this ability during a surprise round. Using a battle plan is a quick action. When a character uses this battle plan, each friendly character in this character\'s command range can immediately make one attack. After these attacks, the surprise round ends and the characters are detected.
Attack as one in surprise round
The character can spend 1 feat point to use this ability. Using a battle plan is a quick action. When a character uses this battle plan, friendly characters gain +2\" movement for the round.

The character can spend 1 feat point to use this ability. Using a battle plan is a quick action. When a character uses this battle plan, each friendly character gains cover, does not suffer blast damage, and does not block LOS until they move, are placed, or are engaged.
Choose which damage column is hit
Once/round, free melee attack when missed
